      <bioghist id="aspace_5ece8cfeffc12005e73ae305e8a9f153">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>John William Tebbel was born in Boyne City, Michigan on November 16, 1912. Following graduation from Central Michigan College of Education (A.B. 1935) and Columbia (M.S. 1937), Tebbel went on to a career as a newspaper journalist, professor of journalism, and author.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_358e63d66cf2bab07db0a36edc394f77">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The John William Tebbel papers consist of a typescript for Tebbel's book <title render="italic">
               <part>George Horace Lorimer and the Saturday Evening Post</part>
            </title>, published by Doubleday &amp; Company in 1948. The typescript contains occasional annotations in the author's hand.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_aca5c897f6e7915b732156f784348529">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
